:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It has come to our attention that =
MeridianLink, in light of a significant breach compromising customer data a=
nd operational information, has failed to file the requisite disclosure und=
er Item 1.05 of Form 8-K within the stipulated four business days, as manda=
ted by the new SEC rules.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Do you think =E2=80=A6=C2=A0do you think the r=
ansomware collective=E2=80=99s lawyers wrote that? Do you think they hired =
a former SEC enforcement lawyer to do their whistleblower submissions? Did =
they have an executive meeting where some ambitious young hacker was like =
=E2=80=9Clook ransom is great but I think we have a real opportunity to exp=
and into the SEC whistleblowing space, it=E2=80=99s pretty simple to add to=
 our current product so we won=E2=80=99t need a ton of engineering resource=
s but to maximize returns we really need to hire someone familiar with the =
SEC=E2=80=9D? If you work at the SEC and are considering a private-sector j=
ob offer from a ransomware collective please, please, please email me about=
 it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are problems with their submission, of c=
ourse:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The Item 1.05 disclosure rules don=E2=
=80=99t go into effect until next month, though those rules largely codify =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33394198.256419/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9kaXZpc2lvbnMvY29ycGZpbi9ndWlkYW5jZS9jZmd1aWRhbmNlL=
