<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Ad valorem</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If Rivian Automotive Inc. bought some land in =
Georgia and built a big factory there, it would have to pay Georgia propert=
y taxes on the factory. If, instead, the government of the state of Georgia=
 bought the land and built the factory there, and Rivian just=C2=A0<em>rent=
ed=C2=A0</em>it from the state, it would not have to pay the taxes.<a class=
=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !=
important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0If Georgia really really wants Rivian to build a factory in Georg=
ia, it might want=C2=A0to give Rivian that=C2=A0tax reduction, as sort of a=
 welcome gift.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But one doesn=E2=80=99t want the gift to be to=
o lavish. The gift is =E2=80=9Cyou don=E2=80=99t have to pay the full prope=
rty tax rate on your factory,=E2=80=9D not =E2=80=9Cwe will literally buy t=
he land and build the factory for you.=E2=80=9D Rivian still has to build t=
he factory! And the specific series of incantations that you utter, in Geor=
gia, to make this all work is<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-=
3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !impor=
tant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Georgia, or more accurately a Georgia=
 government entity called the JDA,<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#foot=
note-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !=
important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;=
">
<span>[4]</span>
</a> agrees to issue=C2=A0up to $15 billion of municipal bonds, from time t=
o time, to pay for the land and construction.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bo=
ttom: 5px;">Rivian agrees to buy the bonds whenever they are issued.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Rivian also agrees to rent the land an=
d factory from the JDA.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Whenever R=
ivian needs to spend a slug of money on the factory, it sends the JDA a not=
ice saying =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99re spending $100 million=E2=80=9D or whateve=
r, and then the JDA sends back a notice saying =E2=80=9Cgreat we=E2=80=99re=
 selling you $100 million of bonds.=E2=80=9D<a class=3D"footnote-index" hre=
f=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inl=
ine-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">And then Rivian just spends the $=
100 million, but everyone agrees that in some entirely abstract sense what =
happened is that Rivian paid $100 million to the JDA to buy bonds, and the =
JDA issued the bonds to Rivian, and the JDA got the money, and the JDA gave=
 the money to Rivian, and Rivian spent it. No actual money changes hands be=
tween Rivian and the JDA; they all just agree to look at Rivian=E2=80=99s s=
pending in a peculiar way.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-6" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !importan=
t; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Of course then the =E2=80=9Cbonds=
=E2=80=9D are =E2=80=9Coutstanding,=E2=80=9D and the JDA =E2=80=9Cowes=E2=
=80=9D Rivian the =E2=80=9C$100 million=E2=80=9D plus =E2=80=9Cinterest,=E2=
=80=9D=C2=A0but this too is completely abstract, and the way it works is, n=
otionally,=C2=A0that Rivian pays the JDA the $100 million plus interest as =
=E2=80=9Crent=E2=80=9D for the factory, and the JDA pays that back to Rivia=
n as =E2=80=9Cprincipal and interest=E2=80=9D on the bonds. Again, no money=
 changes hands either way; this is just a further peculiar way to look at R=
ivian=E2=80=99s spending to make the books balance.<a class=3D"footnote-ind=
ex" href=3D"#footnote-7" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; displ=
ay: inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">At the end of the rental term (in=
 December 2047) Rivian gets to buy the land and factory for $100.<a class=
=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-8" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !=
important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[8]</span>
</a>
</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The result is that, for the term of the agreem=
ent, the JDA=C2=A0<em>technically=C2=A0</em>owns the factory, but Rivian ac=
tually pays to build it. But since it doesn=E2=80=99t own it, it doesn=E2=
=80=99t pay taxes. (It does make negotiated=C2=A0payments in lieu of taxes,=
 but at a lower rate.)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fun! Bloomberg=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33394198.256419/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMTUvcml2aWFuLWxpbmVzLXVwLTE1LWJpbG=
xpb24tZmFrZS1ib25kLXBsYW4tdG8tc25hZy10YXgtYnJlYWs_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTExNjIzX01PT=
kVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09=
MjMxMTE2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6df6c917"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">  Amanda Albright reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Electric-vehicle maker Rivian Automotive Inc. =
released what would usually be a startling announcement for the municipal-f=
inance market: A potential $15 billion bond for a Georgia campus, that woul=
d in theory be the largest ever muni sale and nearly the size of the compan=
y=E2=80=99s market cap.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Except, the bonds aren=E2=80=99t real.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The debt is structured as what=E2=80=99s known=
 as =E2=80=9Cphantom bonds=E2=80=9D that are used by companies to get a pro=
perty tax break in Georgia, and involve no real financial or accounting imp=
act for the company involved, according to a report by law firm Smith, Gamb=
rell &amp; Russell LLP. In Rivian=E2=80=99s case, it=E2=80=99s a workaround=
 because the state doesn=E2=80=99t have legislation allowing for companies =
to get abatements that provide such relief.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The massive =E2=80=94 yet essentially fictitio=
us =E2=80=94 sale is necessary as part of what=E2=80=99s one of the largest=
 economic development projects in Georgia=E2=80=99s history. It=E2=80=99s a=
lso indicative of the fierce arms-race states embark on to land massive man=
ufacturing deals that promise high-paying jobs and an economic boon. The co=
mpany says it will create 7,500 jobs and that once up and running, the faci=
lity will eventually produce as much as 400,000 vehicles per year. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe whole concept is set up for a bre=
ak on the ad-valorem taxes,=E2=80=9D John Shakarjian, Rivian=E2=80=99s asso=
ciate general counsel for real estate and construction, said in an intervie=
w. =E2=80=9CThere=E2=80=99s no cash changing hands, there=E2=80=99s no cash=
 being generated, there=E2=80=99s no movement of money.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Shakarjian said Georgia=E2=80=99s system for e=
conomic development projects was unusual among US states and even among cou=
ntries abroad. He noted it=E2=80=99s common for companies in Georgia to use=
 the phantom-bond structure.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Love it. You could imagine the government of G=
eorgia just saying =E2=80=9Cyou know what, never mind all this,=C2=A0<em>yo=
u=C2=A0</em>just build the factory and we=E2=80=99ll waive your taxes for a=
 bit.=E2=80=9D But apparently that=E2=80=99s not allowed =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=
=80=9Cthe state doesn=E2=80=99t have legislation allowing for companies to =
get abatements=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0so it does this instead. Which comes=
 to the same place, but=C2=A0provides much more entertainment for lawyers, =
and for me.</p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
