<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Elsewhere in whistleblower incentives</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">More generally. Let=E2=80=99s say you find som=
ething bad at a public company that the rest of the market does not know ab=
out. (Let=E2=80=99s say you <em>didn=E2=80=99t</em> do the bad thing yourse=
lf.) Let=E2=80=99s say that you know with certainty that, when you disclose=
 your bad news, the company=E2=80=99s value will decline by 20%. It=E2=80=
=99s a company with a $1 billion market capitalization, and once the market=
 knows about your news it will be worth $800 million. What should you do?</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could sell the stock short. Say you short =
$100 million of stock, tying up roughly $100 million of your balance sheet =
and risk exposure. You publish your news, the market reacts, your position =
declines to $80 million, you cover, you have made $20 million. That is prob=
ably too optimistic; it=E2=80=99s not easy to short 10% of a company=E2=80=
=99s stock, and you=E2=80=99ll probably pay a lot in stock borrow costs.<a =
class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-9" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpar=
ent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[9]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or you could file an SEC whistleblower complai=
nt. How much is that worth to you? Well, the bull case is something like:</=
p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The bad thing cost shareholders $200 =
million.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The SEC will make the com=
pany pay=C2=A0the $200 million of damages as a penalty (and give some of it=
 to the aggrieved shareholders).<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footno=
te-10" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !i=
mportant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;"=
>
<span>[10]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The SEC will give you 30% of the =
damages, or $60 million.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You have made three times as much money, and y=
ou=C2=A0<em>haven=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>tied up $100 million of balance sheet=
, or taken any risk:<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-11" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; ba=
ckground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[11]</span>
</a>If you turn out to be completely wrong about the bad news or the market=
 reaction, you don=E2=80=99t lose any money, whereas if=C2=A0you had shorte=
d you would have.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now, that math is also way too optimistic: The=
 SEC whistleblower program moves a lot more slowly than the market, and the=
re is no guarantee that the SEC will investigate, that they will bring a ca=
se, that they will win (or settle), that they will ask for (or get) anythin=
g like those maximum damages, that they will judge you to be a worthy whist=
leblower, or that they will give you 30% even if they do. (=E2=80=9CWhistle=
blower awards can range from 10 to 30 percent of the money collected when t=
he monetary sanctions exceed $1 million,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33394198.256419/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9=
uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0xNDc/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9e2c0f83" ite=
